#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. Life Span"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Subhasutta"
msgstr "3. Beautiful"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.234"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn4.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhamūle paṭhamābhisambuddho."
msgstr ""
"At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā "
"at the root of the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

msgctxt "sn4.3:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā rattandhakāratimisāyaṃ abbhokāse nisinno "
"hoti, devo ca ekamekaṃ phusāyati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha was meditating in the open during the dark of "
"night, while a gentle rain drizzled down."

# The phrase is identical with SN 2.29, and i don’t see why we should follow BB in using “color” there and “shape” here for vanna.
msgctxt "sn4.3:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā, bhagavato bhayaṃ chambhitattaṃ lomahaṃsaṃ "
"uppādetukāmo, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato avidūre "
"uccāvacā vaṇṇanibhā upadaṃseti, subhā ceva asubhā ca."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked, wanting to make the Buddha feel fear, terror, and "
"goosebumps, approached him, and while not far away generated a rainbow of "
"bright colors, both beautiful and ugly."

msgctxt "sn4.3:1.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.1"
msgid "“Saṃsaraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Transmigrating for such a long time,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.2"
msgid "vaṇṇaṃ katvā subhāsubhaṃ;"
msgstr "you’ve made forms beautiful and ugly."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.3"
msgid "Alaṃ te tena pāpima,"
msgstr "Enough of this, Wicked One!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:2.4"
msgid "nihato tvamasi antaka."
msgstr "You’re defeated, terminator."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.1"
msgid "Ye ca kāyena vācāya,"
msgstr "Those who are well restrained"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.2"
msgid "manasā ca susaṃvutā;"
msgstr "in body, speech, and mind"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.3"
msgid "Na te māravasānugā,"
msgstr "don’t fall under Māra’s sway,"

# See BB for reading.
#. <br>
#. VAR: baddhagū → paccagū (si, s1-3, km, pts1) | paddhagūti (pts2) | baddhabhū (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.3:3.4"
msgid "na te mārassa baddhagū”ti."
msgstr "they don’t become your henchmen.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.3:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro … pe … tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr "Then Māra … vanished right there."
